[According to Worldometer accessed on 7 May 2020, 22:00 EDT, Peru having reported 58 526 cases including 1627 deaths, is number 13 globally for cumulative numbers of cases of COVID-19. The 1st imported case into Peru was reported on 6 Mar 2020. Iquitos is the capital of the Loreto region; it is located at the confluence of the Amazon, Nanay, and Itaya Rivers, and is a port city in the Amazon region. It has an estimated population of less than half a million inhabitants. It is accessible only by air or boat. This creates the challenges of supplying the city's health sector with needed supplies and makes a surge capacity even more difficult to implement. - Mod.MPP

