ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to Worldometer, Brazil is number 8 globally having reported a cumulative total of 135 773 cases including 9190 deaths. The 1st imported case into Brazil was reported on 26 Feb 2020. Manaus is located in the North of Brazil in the Amazonas State. To the east of the city is the confluence of the Negro River where it converges with the Solimoes River -- tributaries of the Amazonas River. There is an estimated population of over 2 million inhabitants. It is in the middle of the large tropical rainforest and is a takeoff point for many Amazon region explorations and tourism. Noting the differences in the 2 cities (Iquitos in Peru and Manaus in Brazil, the outcomes of the COVID-19 pandemic have many similarities, with an overload of the health infrastructure, shortages of needed supplies, and high mortality as an outcome. - Mod.MPP

